      <hedline>
        <hl1>Always Time for Her Baby</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Michelle Bernstein, who was profiled in Jan 24 article about chefs, contends she is almost always at her restaurant Michy's</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I would appreciate it if people disregarded the statement in the article ''Follow the Money All the Way to the Kitchen'' (Jan. 24) that I am almost never at my restaurant Michy's. We created Michy's with our own hands; it's our first baby and our livelihood. The thought of my not spending time in our restaurant is impossible to conceive. It is what I love most: the heat, the creativity and the insanity.</p>
        <p>Michelle Bernstein  Miami</p>
        <p>The writer is the chef and a partner in Michy's.</p>
      </block>
